1. Introduction

1.1. Metadata

  1. DATABASE PENELITIAN PNEUMOKOKUS (Manado, Lombok, Sorong, Sumbawa).xlsx: An Excel file separated by sheets for every region (focused on Lombok and Sumbawa, but also including Manado and Papua). Within the excel file there are information about ongoing WGS preparation for troublematic samples (the need confirmation sheets)
  2. Data WGS_Lombok.xlsx: An information storage for in silico WGS results for Lombok samples (Sumbawa is not available yet)

1.2. Fasta data

324 files of WGS stored in *.fasta format (including the metadata) were shared to me at 11 March 2025, consisting of 189 Lombok files and 135 Sumbawa files. Unfortunately, I have found 49 files with naming inconsistenciesthese files are not match to their SPECIMEN ID in metadata.

I copy these files in a separated folder, then perform a manual rename by adding underscore (_) between region code (LBK OR SWQ) and ID number.
